text_run.content: In this reference, you can find descriptions of monitoring metrics for Zilliz Cloud clusters, as well as alert targets that you can set up at organization and project levels.
tab in the Zilliz Cloud console presents various graphical representations.
The table provides a description of each metric and the actions that you are advised to perform when the usage of your cluster resource exceeds a threshold.
Currently, serverless clusters offer only one metric, CU Capacity. To unlock a wide range of advanced metrics,

The network inbound flow of pod.

Project alerts focus on the operational aspects of your clusters, including notifications on the CU usage, QPS thresholds, latency issues, and request anomalies, ensuring you maintain optimal cluster performance.
Zilliz Cloud predefines common alert targets to ensure that critical issues are quickly identified and addressed with the appropriate actions.
For more information about recommended actions, refer to
: Trigger alerts at >70% utilized computational power for 10+ minutes.
: Trigger alerts at >90% utilized computational power for 10+ minutes.
: Trigger alerts at >70% utilized CU capacity for 10+ minutes.
: Trigger alerts at >90% utilized CU capacity for 10+ minutes.
alerts at >50 search operations per second for 10+ minutes.
alerts at >50 query operations per second for 10+ minutes.
alerts at P99 latency >1,000ms for 10+ minutes.
alerts at P99 latency >1,000ms for 10+ minutes.
In addition to the predefined default project alerts , you can also configure custom alert targets as needed.
